```class Solution {
public:
    string robotWithString(string s) {
        string t = "";
        while (s.length() > 0) {
            t = s + t;
            s.erase(s.begin());
        }
        return t;
    }
};
```

efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW

Explanation:
The algorithm iterates through the string s until it becomes empty. In each iteration, it appends the string s to t and removes the first character from s. Since the string length decreases by 1 in each iteration, the time complexity is O(n), where n is the length of the string. The space complexity is O(1) because we only use a constant amount of space for the string t. The energy implications are low because the algorithm only performs a few simple operations.

